---
# agent-ready config. Copy to .claude/agent-ready.local.md in your repo and tune.
# All keys are optional; omitted keys use the defaults shown.

# Max lines before the file-size hook reacts.
line_budget: 400

# What the PreToolUse file-size hook does when a file is over budget:
#   warn  - advisory note, never blocks (default)
#   block - deny the write/edit until the file is split
#   off   - do nothing
file_size_rule: warn

# How many commits since CLAUDE.md/AGENTS.md were last touched before the
# SessionStart hook calls the context files stale.
context_drift_commits: 15

# Paths excluded from the file-size check (minimal ** / * globs).
ignore:
  - "**/node_modules/**"
  - "**/vendor/**"
  - "**/dist/**"
  - "**/build/**"
  - "**/*.min.js"
  - "**/*.gen.go"
  - "**/*.pb.go"
---

# agent-ready (local config)

This file configures the `agent-ready` plugin for this repo. The YAML frontmatter
above is what the hooks read; this body is just notes for humans.
